<subSubSection id="FD9102D0ED02FF80FF54FBC5FBC6F8F6" pageId="16" pageNumber="167" type="description">
<paragraph id="B534515BED02FF80FF54FBC5FAC1FA5E" blockId="16.[151,1437,1139,1923]" pageId="16" pageNumber="167">
<emphasis id="87FF8D49ED02FF80FF54FBC5FE26FB26" bold="true" box="[199,420,1139,1166]" pageId="16" pageNumber="167">Description. Male.</emphasis>
Habitus as shown in 
<figureCitation id="2DB04DDEED02FF80FD0BFBC2FC98FB26" box="[664,794,1140,1166]" captionStart="FIGURES 77–83" captionStartId="15.[151,264,1894,1918]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,993,1871]" captionTargetId="figure-337@15.[151,1436,993,1871]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURES 77–83. Charippus denjii Yu, Maddison &amp; Zhang, sp. nov., male (77, 79–80, 82) and female (78, 81, 83). 77–79. Habitus, in dorsal (77–78) and ventral (79) view; 80–81. Front view of carapace; 82–83. Details of chelicera, apical (82) and back view (83), arrows pointing to triangular projections." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6500790" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6500790/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="167">Figs 77, 79</figureCitation>
. Carapace length 1.96 (variation: 1.96–2.05, n=4); abdomen length 2.06. Measurements of eyes: AME 0.35, ALE 0.29, PME 0.06, PLE 0.24. Measurements of legs: I 3.13 (0.96, 0.51, 0.78, 0.50, 0.38), II 2.83 (0.90, 0.43, 0.64, 0.48, 0.38), III 2.96 (0.89, 0.36, 0.64, 0.61, 0.46), IV 3.36 (1.00, 0.40, 0.79, 0.72, 0.45). Chelicerae dark brown, distally with small triangular projection, promargin with two teeth, retromargin with one bicuspid tooth. Palp (
<figureCitation id="2DB04DDEED02FF80FD57FAB2FCCAFAB6" box="[708,840,1284,1310]" captionStart-0="FIGURES 84–86" captionStart-1="FIGURES 87–89" captionStartId-0="16.[151,264,1033,1057]" captionStartId-1="17.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox-0="[162,1430,181,1003]" captionTargetBox-1="[199,1400,190,1904]" captionTargetId-0="figure-19@16.[151,1436,181,1009]" captionTargetId-1="figure-19@17.[181,1406,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId-0="16" captionTargetPageId-1="17" captionText-0="FIGURES 84–86. Palp of Charippus denjii Yu, Maddison &amp; Zhang, sp. nov., holotype, in prolateral (84), ventral (85) and retrolateral (86) view." captionText-1="FIGURES 87–89. Palp of Charippus denjii Yu, Maddison &amp; Zhang, sp. nov., holotype, in ventral (87), retrolateral (88) and dorsal (89) view." figureDoi-0="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6500793" figureDoi-1="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6500795" httpUri-0="https://zenodo.org/record/6500793/files/figure.png" httpUri-1="https://zenodo.org/record/6500795/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="167">Figs 84–89</figureCitation>
): yellowish brown; bulb bulging; embolus coiled for more than a circle, with a row of sawtooth-like denticles; embolic disc large and sclerotized, centrally concave, with many small grooves; LED wide and outer-extended, serrulate-edged; tegulum slightly sclerotized, without prominent tegular lobe; salticid radix slightly sclerotized; retrolateral sperm duct loop indistinct in ventral view; retrolateral tibial apophysis thick and wide, slightly curved, distally bifurcated. Sternum without setal tuft. Color in alcohol (
<figureCitation id="2DB04DDEED02FF80FF0CFA0EFEA2FA7A" box="[159,288,1464,1490]" captionStart="FIGURES 77–83" captionStartId="15.[151,264,1894,1918]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,993,1871]" captionTargetId="figure-337@15.[151,1436,993,1871]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURES 77–83. Charippus denjii Yu, Maddison &amp; Zhang, sp. nov., male (77, 79–80, 82) and female (78, 81, 83). 77–79. Habitus, in dorsal (77–78) and ventral (79) view; 80–81. Front view of carapace; 82–83. Details of chelicera, apical (82) and back view (83), arrows pointing to triangular projections." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6500790" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6500790/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="167">Figs 77, 79</figureCitation>
): carapace dark brown, CPSB present, frontally white; dorsal abdomen pale with dark brown markings; abdomen with obviously sclerotized areas dorsally and ventrally. Legs I–II slightly darker than legs III–IV.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="B534515BED02FF80FF54F9B6FECDF8BE" blockId="16.[151,1437,1139,1923]" pageId="16" pageNumber="167">
<emphasis id="87FF8D49ED02FF80FF54F9B6FEA7F9B2" bold="true" box="[199,293,1536,1562]" pageId="16" pageNumber="167">Female.</emphasis>
Habitus as shown in 
<figureCitation id="2DB04DDEED02FF80FD84F9B6FDE8F9B2" box="[535,618,1536,1562]" captionStart="FIGURES 77–83" captionStartId="15.[151,264,1894,1918]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,993,1871]" captionTargetId="figure-337@15.[151,1436,993,1871]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURES 77–83. Charippus denjii Yu, Maddison &amp; Zhang, sp. nov., male (77, 79–80, 82) and female (78, 81, 83). 77–79. Habitus, in dorsal (77–78) and ventral (79) view; 80–81. Front view of carapace; 82–83. Details of chelicera, apical (82) and back view (83), arrows pointing to triangular projections." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6500790" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6500790/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="167">Fig. 78</figureCitation>
. Carapace length 2.16 (variation: 1.86–2.16, n=4); abdomen length 2.64. Measurements of eyes: AME 0.37, ALE 0.22, PME 0.06, PLE 0.23. Measurements of legs: I 3.15 (0.99, 0.55, 0.73, 0.50, 0.38), II 2.86 (0.94, 0.51, 0.64, 0.44, 0.33), III 3.28 (1.07, 0.45, 0.68, 0.68, 0.40), IV 3.90 (1.16, 0.53, 0.85, 0.88, 0.48). Chelicerae (
<figureCitation id="2DB04DDEED02FF80FE77F9DAFDB4F92E" box="[484,566,1644,1670]" captionStart="FIGURES 77–83" captionStartId="15.[151,264,1894,1918]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,993,1871]" captionTargetId="figure-337@15.[151,1436,993,1871]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURES 77–83. Charippus denjii Yu, Maddison &amp; Zhang, sp. nov., male (77, 79–80, 82) and female (78, 81, 83). 77–79. Habitus, in dorsal (77–78) and ventral (79) view; 80–81. Front view of carapace; 82–83. Details of chelicera, apical (82) and back view (83), arrows pointing to triangular projections." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6500790" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6500790/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="167">Fig. 83</figureCitation>
) as in male but without small triangular projection distally. Abdomen without sclerotized areas. Color in alcohol (
<figureCitation id="2DB04DDEED02FF80FDBFF926FDFCF902" box="[556,638,1680,1706]" captionStart="FIGURES 77–83" captionStartId="15.[151,264,1894,1918]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,993,1871]" captionTargetId="figure-337@15.[151,1436,993,1871]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURES 77–83. Charippus denjii Yu, Maddison &amp; Zhang, sp. nov., male (77, 79–80, 82) and female (78, 81, 83). 77–79. Habitus, in dorsal (77–78) and ventral (79) view; 80–81. Front view of carapace; 82–83. Details of chelicera, apical (82) and back view (83), arrows pointing to triangular projections." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6500790" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6500790/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="167">Fig. 78</figureCitation>
) as in male. Sternum without setal tuft centrally. Epigynum (
<figureCitation id="2DB04DDEED02FF80FAAAF926FF35F966" captionStart="FIGURES 90–94" captionStartId="18.[151,264,1687,1711]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,182,1644]" captionTargetId="figure-19@18.[151,1436,181,1663]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="FIGURES 90–94. Female genitalia of Charippus denjii Yu, Maddison &amp; Zhang, sp. nov.. 90, 92. Ventral view; 91, 93. Dorsal view; 94. CD path." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6500797" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6500797/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="167">Figs. 90, 92</figureCitation>
): window large, rims sclerotized and wide, median septum present; lateral depressions shallow and not obvious. Vulva (
<figureCitation id="2DB04DDEED02FF80FF78F96EFEFBF95A" box="[235,377,1752,1778]" captionStart="FIGURES 90–94" captionStartId="18.[151,264,1687,1711]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,182,1644]" captionTargetId="figure-19@18.[151,1436,181,1663]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="FIGURES 90–94. Female genitalia of Charippus denjii Yu, Maddison &amp; Zhang, sp. nov.. 90, 92. Ventral view; 91, 93. Dorsal view; 94. CD path." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6500797" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6500797/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="167">Figs. 91, 93</figureCitation>
): CD long and coiled, swerving for six times; AG chilli-like, pointing to axis; spermathecae slightly bulging.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="B534515BED02FF80FF54F896FBC6F8F6" blockId="16.[151,1437,1139,1923]" pageId="16" pageNumber="167">
<emphasis id="87FF8D49ED02FF80FF54F896FE0AF891" bold="true" box="[199,392,1823,1850]" pageId="16" pageNumber="167">Natural history.</emphasis>
One female specimen collected in March from Wuzhishan City was observed guarding an egg-sac under the moss of a vertical rock, and the egg-sac only had 
<specimenCount id="A38D9AD2ED02FF80FC1DF8F2FC70F8F6" box="[910,1010,1860,1886]" pageId="16" pageNumber="167" type="egg">two eggs</specimenCount>
inside.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
